msgstr "Theravāda Collection on Monastic Law"

#. </p><p class="division"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss3:pts-cs0.2"
msgid "Mahāvibhaṅga"
msgstr "Monks’ rules and their analysis"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss3:pts-cs0.3"
msgid "Saṃ­ghā­di­sesa­kaṇḍa"
msgstr "Monks’ Suspension"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss3:pts-cs0.4"
msgid "Duṭṭhul­la­vācā­sikkhā­pada"
msgstr "3. The training rule on lewd speech"

#. </h1></div><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss3:pts-cs1.1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Origin story"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="1"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.128"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.214"></a><a class="pts-cs-empty" id="bu-ss.3.1"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-ss.3.1.1"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1133"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss3:pts-cs1.1.1"
msgid ""
"Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anātha­piṇḍi­"
"kassa ārāme."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, "
"Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss3:pts-cs1.1.2"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā udāyī araññe viharati."
msgstr "At that time Venerable Udāyī was staying in the wilderness,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss3:pts-cs1.1.3"
msgid "Tassāyasmato vihāro abhirūpo hoti dassanīyo pāsādiko."
msgstr "in a beautiful dwelling."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss3:pts-cs1.1.4"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena sambahulā itthiyo ārāmaṃ āgamaṃsu vihā­ra­pekkhi­kāyo."
msgstr "Just then a number of women came to the monastery to see the dwellings."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss3:pts-cs1.1.5"
msgid "Atha kho tā itthiyo yenāyasmā udāyī tenu­pasaṅka­miṃsu;"
msgstr "They approached Udāyī"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss3:pts-cs1.1.6"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ udāyiṃ etadavocuṃ—"
msgstr "and said,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss3:pts-cs1.1.7"
msgid "“icchāma mayaṃ, bhante, ayyassa vihāraṃ pekkhitun”ti."
msgstr "“Venerable, we would like to see your dwelling.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss3:pts-cs1.1.8"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā udāyī tā itthiyo vihāraṃ pekkhāpetvā tāsaṃ itthīnaṃ "
"vaccamaggaṃ passāvamaggaṃ ādissa vaṇṇampi bhaṇati avaṇṇampi bhaṇati yācatipi "
"āyācatipi pucchatipi paṭipucchatipi ācikkhatipi anusāsatipi akkosatipi."
msgstr ""
"Then, after showing them his own dwelling, he praised and disparaged their "
"private parts; he requested and implored, asked and enquired, described, "
"instructed, and abused."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss3:pts-cs1.1.9"
msgid ""
"Yā tā itthiyo chinnikā dhuttikā ahirikāyo tā āyasmatā udāyinā saddhiṃ "
"uhasantipi ullapantipi ujjagghantipi uppaṇḍentipi."
msgstr ""
"Those women among them who were wanton and shameless flirted with Udāyī; "
"they called out to him, laughed with him, and made fun of him."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss3:pts-cs1.1.10"
msgid "Yā pana tā itthiyo hirimanā tā nikkhamitvā bhikkhū ujjhāpenti—"
msgstr ""
"But, after leaving, those among them who had a sense of shame complained to "
"the monks,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss3:pts-cs1.1.11"
msgid "“idaṃ, bhante, nacchannaṃ nappatirūpaṃ."
msgstr "“Venerables, this isn’t suitable and appropriate."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss3:pts-cs1.1.12"
msgid "Sāmikenapi mayaṃ evaṃ vuttā na iccheyyāma, kiṃ panāyyena udāyinā”ti."
msgstr ""
"We wouldn’t want to hear this from our own husbands, let alone from "
"Venerable Udāyī.”"

#. </p><p><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-ss.3.1.2"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss3:pts-cs1.2.1"
msgid "Ye te bhikkhū appicchā … pe …"
msgstr "The monks of few desires …"

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.215"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss3:pts-cs1.2.2"
msgid "te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "complained and criticized him,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss3:pts-cs1.2.3"
msgid ""
"“kathañhi nāma āyasmā udāyī mātugāmaṃ duṭṭhullāhi vācāhi obhāsissatī”ti."
msgstr "“How can Venerable Udāyī speak lewdly to women?”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="2"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1134"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss3:pts-cs1.2.4"
msgid ""
"Atha kho te bhikkhū āyasmantaṃ udāyiṃ aneka­pariyā­yena vigarahitvā "
"bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ."
msgstr "They rebuked Udāyī in many ways and told the Master."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss3:pts-cs1.2.5"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe bhikkhusaṃghaṃ "
"sannipātāpetvā āyasmantaṃ udāyiṃ paṭipucchi—"
msgstr "And the Master had the Order of monks assembled and questioned Udāyī,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss3:pts-cs1.2.6"
msgid "“saccaṃ kira tvaṃ, udāyi, mātugāmaṃ duṭṭhullāhi vācāhi obhāsasī”ti?"
msgstr "“Is it true, Udāyī, that you spoke lewdly to women?”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss3:pts-cs1.2.7"
msgid "“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss3:pts-cs1.2.8"
msgid "Vigarahi buddho bhagavā—"
msgstr "The Buddha rebuked him,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss3:pts-cs1.2.9"
msgid ""
"“ananucchavikaṃ, moghapurisa, ananulomikaṃ appatirūpaṃ assāmaṇakaṃ akappiyaṃ "
"akaraṇīyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"“It’s not suitable, foolish man, it’s not proper, it’s not worthy of a "
"recluse, it’s not allowable, it should not to be done."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss3:pts-cs1.2.10"
msgid ""
"Kathañhi nāma tvaṃ, moghapurisa, mātugāmaṃ duṭṭhullāhi vācāhi obhāsissasi."
msgstr "How can you speak lewdly to women?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss3:pts-cs1.2.11"
msgid ""
"Nanu mayā, moghapurisa, aneka­pariyā­yena virāgāya dhammo desito no sarāgāya "
"… pe …"
msgstr ""
"Haven’t I given many teachings for the sake of dispassion, not for the sake "
"of passion …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss3:pts-cs1.2.12"
msgid "kāma­pari­ḷāhā­naṃ vūpasamo akkhāto."
msgstr "for the stilling of the fevers of sense desire?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss3:pts-cs1.2.13"
msgid "Netaṃ, moghapurisa, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya … pe …"
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss3:pts-cs1.2.14"
msgid "evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss3:pts-cs1.2.14a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Final ruling"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="3"></a>
#. <span class="rule"> 
#. VAR: yathā taṃ → yathātaṃ (s1-3)
#. VAR: methu­nu­pa­saṃhi­tāhi → methu­nū­pa­sañ­hi­tāhi (bj, s1-3)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss3:pts-cs1.2.15"
msgid ""
"“Yo pana bhikkhu otiṇṇo vipariṇatena cittena mātugāmaṃ duṭṭhullāhi vācāhi "
"obhāseyya yathā taṃ yuvā yuvatiṃ methu­nu­pa­saṃhi­tāhi, saṃghādiseso”ti."
msgstr ""
"‘If a lustful monk speaks lewd words connected with sexual intercourse to a "
"woman, as a young man might to a young woman, he commits an offense "
"entailing suspension.’”"

#. </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss3:pts-cs1.2.16"
msgid "(<em>3</em>:<strong>7</strong>)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss3:pts-cs2.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Definitions"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="4"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-ss.3.2"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1136"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss3:pts-cs2.1"
msgid "Yo panāti"
msgstr "A:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss3:pts-cs2.2"
msgid "yo yādiso … pe …"
msgstr "whoever …"

#. </span>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss3:pts-cs2.3"
msgid "bhikkhūti"
msgstr "Monk:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss3:pts-cs2.4"
msgid "… pe …"
msgstr ""
"… The monk who has been given the full ordination by a complete Order "
"through a procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is "
"unchallengeable and fit to stand—"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss3:pts-cs2.5"
msgid "ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti."
msgstr "this sort of monk is meant in this case."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="5"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1137"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss3:pts-cs2.6"
msgid "Otiṇṇo nāma"
msgstr "Lustful:"

#. </span>
#. I have rendered <i lang="pli">otiṇṇo vipariṇatena cittena</i> with the single word “lustful.” This means that the definition for <i lang="pli">vipariṇataṃ</i> is missing from my translation. Here is the Pali, followed by a translation: <i lang="pli">Vipariṇatanti rattampi cittaṃ vipariṇataṃ. Duṭṭhampi cittaṃ vipariṇataṃ. Mūḷhampi cittaṃ vipariṇataṃ. Api ca rattaṃ cittaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippetaṃ vipariṇatanti</i>; “distorted: a mind with desire is distorted, a mind with anger is distorted, a confused mind is distorted. But in this case ‘distorted’ refers to a mind with desire.”
#. <span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss3:pts-cs2.7"
msgid "sāratto apekkhavā paṭi­baddha­citto."
msgstr "having lust, longing for, in love with."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="6"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1138"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss3:pts-cs2.8"
msgid "Vipariṇatanti"
msgstr ""

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss3:pts-cs2.9"
msgid ""
"rattampi cittaṃ vipariṇataṃ, duṭṭhampi cittaṃ vipariṇataṃ mūḷhampi cittaṃ "
"vipariṇataṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss3:pts-cs2.10"
msgid "Api ca rattaṃ cittaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippetaṃ vipariṇatanti."
msgstr ""

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="7"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1139"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss3:pts-cs2.11"
msgid "Mātugāmo nāma"
msgstr "A woman:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss3:pts-cs2.12"
msgid "manussitthī, na yakkhī, na petī, na tiracchānagatā."
msgstr ""
"a human female, not a female spirit, not a female ghost, not a female animal."

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.216"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss3:pts-cs2.13"
msgid ""
"Viññū paṭibalā subhā­sita­dub­bhāsi­taṃ duṭṭhul­lā­duṭṭhul­laṃ ājānituṃ."
msgstr ""
"She understands and is capable of discerning bad speech and good speech, "
"what is lewd and what is not lewd."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="8"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1140"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss3:pts-cs2.14"
msgid "Duṭṭhullā nāma"
msgstr "Lewd words:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1141"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss3:pts-cs2.15"
msgid "vācā vacca­magga­passā­va­magga­me­thuna­dhammap­paṭi­saṃ­yuttā vācā."
msgstr "speech connected with the anus, the vagina, or sexual intercourse."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="9"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss3:pts-cs2.16"
msgid "Obhāseyyāti"
msgstr "Speaks:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss3:pts-cs2.17"
msgid "ajjhācāro vuccati."
msgstr "misconduct is what is meant."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="10"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1142"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss3:pts-cs2.18"
msgid "Yathā taṃ yuvā yuvatinti"
msgstr "As a young man might to a young woman:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss3:pts-cs2.19"
msgid "daharo dahariṃ, taruṇo taruṇiṃ, kāmabhogī kāmabhoginiṃ."
msgstr ""
"a male youth to a female youth, a boy to a girl, a male indulging in sense "
"pleasures to a female indulging in sense pleasures."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="11"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.129"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1143"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss3:pts-cs2.20"
msgid "Methu­nu­pa­saṃhi­tāhīti"
msgstr "Connected with sexual intercourse:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss3:pts-cs2.21"
msgid "methuna­dhammap­paṭi­saṃ­yuttāhi."
msgstr "connected with the sexual act."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="12"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1144"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss3:pts-cs2.22"
msgid "Saṃghādisesoti"
msgstr "He commits an offense entailing suspension:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss3:pts-cs2.23"
msgid "… pe … tenapi vuccati saṃghādisesoti."
msgstr "… Therefore, too, it is called “an offense entailing suspension.”"

#. </span>
#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss3:pts-cs3.1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Permutations"

#. </h2><h4>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss3:pts-cs3.1.0b"
msgid ""
msgstr "Summary"

#. </h4><p><a class="sc" id="13"></a><a class="pts-cs-empty" id="bu-ss.3.3"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-ss.3.3.1"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1145"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss3:pts-cs3.1.1"
msgid ""
"Dve magge ādissa vaṇṇampi bhaṇati, avaṇṇampi bhaṇati, yācatipi, āyācatipi, "
"pucchatipi, paṭipucchatipi, ācikkhatipi, anusāsatipi, akkosatipi."
msgstr ""
"Referring to the two private orifices, he praises, disparages, requests, "
"implores, asks, enquires, describes, instructs, abuses."

#. </p><h4>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss3:pts-cs3.1.1a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Sub-definitions"

#. </h4><p><a class="sc" id="14"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1146"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss3:pts-cs3.1.2"
msgid "Vaṇṇaṃ bhaṇati nāma"
msgstr "Praises:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss3:pts-cs3.1.3"
msgid "dve magge thometi vaṇṇeti pasaṃsati."
msgstr "extols, praises, commends the two private orifices."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="15"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1147"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss3:pts-cs3.1.4"
msgid "Avaṇṇaṃ bhaṇati nāma"
msgstr "Disparages:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss3:pts-cs3.1.5"
msgid "dve magge khuṃseti vambheti garahati."
msgstr "despises, reviles, censures the two private orifices."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="16"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss3:pts-cs3.1.6"
msgid "Yācati nāma"
msgstr "Requests:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss3:pts-cs3.1.7"
msgid "dehi me, arahasi me dātunti."
msgstr "saying, “Give to me; you should to give to me.”"

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="17"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1149"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss3:pts-cs3.1.8"
msgid "Āyācati nāma"
msgstr "Implores:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
#. VAR: kadā → kadā te (s1-3)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss3:pts-cs3.1.9"
msgid "kadā te mātā pasīdissati,"
msgstr "saying, “When will you please your mother?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss3:pts-cs3.1.10"
msgid "kadā te pitā pasīdissati,"
msgstr "When will you please your father?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss3:pts-cs3.1.11"
msgid "kadā te devatāyo pasīdissanti,"
msgstr "When will you please the gods?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss3:pts-cs3.1.12"
msgid "kadā sukhaṇo sulayo sumuhutto bhavissati,"
msgstr "When will there be a good opportunity, a good time, a good moment?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss3:pts-cs3.1.13"
msgid "kadā te methunaṃ dhammaṃ labhissāmīti."
msgstr "When will I have sexual intercourse with you?”"

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="18"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1150"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss3:pts-cs3.1.14"
msgid "Pucchati nāma"
msgstr "Asks:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss3:pts-cs3.1.15"
msgid "kathaṃ tvaṃ sāmikassa desi,"
msgstr "saying, “How do you give to your husband?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss3:pts-cs3.1.16"
msgid "kathaṃ jārassa desīti?"
msgstr "How do you give to your lover?”"

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="19"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1151"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.217"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss3:pts-cs3.1.17"
msgid "Paṭipucchati nāma"
msgstr "Enquires:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss3:pts-cs3.1.18"
msgid "evaṃ kira tvaṃ sāmikassa desi,"
msgstr "saying, “So you give to your husband like this,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss3:pts-cs3.1.19"
msgid "evaṃ jārassa desīti."
msgstr "and to your lover like this?”"

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="20"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1152"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss3:pts-cs3.1.20"
msgid "Ācikkhati nāma"
msgstr "Describes:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss3:pts-cs3.1.21"
